Tracks 8 and 9 were recorded on April 1st, 1959
Tracks 1-5, 7, and 10-12 were recorded on May 4, 1959
Track 6 was recorded on December 2, 1959



Personnel:

Tenor Saxophone, John Coltrane
Piano, Cedar Walton, Tommy Flanagan, Wynton Kelly 
Bass, Paul Chambers
Drums, Art Taylor, Jimmy Cobb, Lex Humphries



Coltrane made two giant steps in 1959: playing on Miles Davis' Kind of Blue and recording his first classic, Giant Steps. 
A truly great Jazz record, an astonishing tenor-saxophone improvisation.



Straight, no chaser.
